// Red-Black Tree Node Structure
template <typename T>
struct RBNode {
    T data;             // The value stored in the node
    bool isRed;         // Color of the node (true = red, false = black)
    RBNode* left;       // Pointer to the left child
    RBNode* right;      // Pointer to the right child
    RBNode* parent;     // Pointer to the parent node

    // Constructor to initialize a node with data and default color (red)
    RBNode(const T& val) : data(val), isRed(true), left(nullptr), right(nullptr), parent(nullptr) {}
};

In a Red-Black Tree, the `isRed` attribute tracks the node's color, which is critical for maintaining balance. Red nodes cannot have red children (to avoid consecutive reds), and the tree must maintain black height consistency. The `parent` pointer is essential for rotations and recoloring operations.
